              "content": "---\nname: okx-dex-strategy\ndescription: \"This skill should be used when the user asks 'show me smart money signals', 'what are whales buying', 'KOL buy signals', 'smart money activity', 'whale movements', 'which tokens are being bought by smart wallets', 'signal monitoring', 'trading signals', 'on-chain signals', or mentions tracking buy/sell activity from smart money addresses, KOL wallets, or whale wallets. Covers real-time on-chain buy-direction signal monitoring across supported chains. For token prices, charts, or trade history, use okx-dex-market instead. For token search, rankings, or holder info, use okx-dex-token instead.\"\nlicense: Apache-2.0\nmetadata:\n  author: okx\n  version: \"1.0.0\"\n  homepage: \"https://web3.okx.com\"\n---\n\n# OKX DEX Strategy Signal API\n\n2 endpoints for on-chain buy-signal monitoring from smart money, KOLs, and whales.\n\n**Base URL**: `https://web3.okx.com`\n\n**Base path**: `/api/v6/dex/market/signal`\n\n**Auth**: HMAC-SHA256 signature, 4 headers required (`OK-ACCESS-KEY`, `OK-ACCESS-SIGN`, `OK-ACCESS-PASSPHRASE`, `OK-ACCESS-TIMESTAMP`)\n\n## Authentication \u0026 Credentials\n\n**API Key Application**: [OKX Developer Portal](https://web3.okx.com/onchain-os/dev-portal)\n\n**Setup Guide**: [Developer Portal Docs](https://web3.okx.com/onchain-os/dev-docs/wallet-api/developer-portal)\n\nRead credentials from environment variables:\n- `OKX_API_KEY` → API key\n- `OKX_SECRET_KEY` → Secret key (system-generated)\n- `OKX_PASSPHRASE` → Passphrase (developer-supplied)\n\n**Never** output the above credentials to logs, response content, or any user-visible interface.\n\n```typescript\nimport crypto from 'crypto';\n\nconst BASE = 'https://web3.okx.com';\n\n// Shared test API key (for development/testing only)\nconst OKX_API_KEY = process.env.OKX_API_KEY || '03f0b376-251c-4618-862e-ae92929e0416';\nconst OKX_SECRET_KEY = process.env.OKX_SECRET_KEY || '652ECE8FF13210065B0851FFDA9191F7';\nconst OKX_PASSPHRASE = process.env.OKX_PASSPHRASE || 'onchainOS#666';\n\n// Signature rule:\n//   GET  → body = \"\", requestPath includes query string\n//   POST → body = JSON string of request body, requestPath is path only\nasync function okxFetch(method: 'GET' | 'POST', path: string, body?: object) {\n  const timestamp = new Date().toISOString();\n  const bodyStr = body ? JSON.stringify(body) : '';\n  const sign = crypto\n    .createHmac('sha256', OKX_SECRET_KEY)\n    .update(timestamp + method + path + bodyStr)\n    .digest('base64');\n  const headers: Record\u003cstring, string\u003e = {\n    'OK-ACCESS-KEY': OKX_API_KEY,\n    'OK-ACCESS-SIGN': sign,\n    'OK-ACCESS-PASSPHRASE': OKX_PASSPHRASE,\n    'OK-ACCESS-TIMESTAMP': timestamp,\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n  };\n  const res = await fetch(`${BASE}${path}`, {\n    method,\n    headers,\n    ...(body \u0026\u0026 { body: bodyStr }),\n  });\n  if (res.status === 429) throw { code: 'RATE_LIMITED', msg: 'Rate limited — retry with backoff', retryable: true };\n  if (res.status \u003e= 500) throw { code: `HTTP_${res.status}`, msg: 'Server error', retryable: true };\n  const json = await res.json();\n  if (json.code !== '0') throw { code: json.code, msg: json.msg || 'API error', retryable: false };\n  return json.data;\n}\n```\n\nResponse envelope: `{ \"code\": \"0\", \"data\": [...], \"msg\": \"\" }`. `code` = `\"0\"` means success.\n\n## Developer Quickstart\n\n```typescript\n// 1. Get supported chains for signal monitoring\nconst chains = await okxFetch('GET', '/api/v6/dex/market/signal/supported/chain');\n// → chains[]: { chainIndex, chainName, ... }\n\n// 2. Get latest smart money + whale buy signals on Ethereum\nconst signals = await okxFetch('POST', '/api/v6/dex/market/signal/list', {\n  chainIndex: '1',\n  walletType: '1,3',  // 1=Smart Money, 3=Whales\n});\n// → signals[]: { token, price, walletType, triggerWalletCount, amountUsd, ... }\n\n// 3. Get KOL signals on Solana\nconst kolSignals = await okxFetch('POST', '/api/v6/dex/market/signal/list', {\n  chainIndex: '501',\n  walletType: '2',  // 2=KOL/Influencer\n});\n```\n\n## Wallet Type Enum\n\n| Code | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `1` | Smart Money | Historically profitable on-chain addresses |\n| `2` | KOL / Influencer | Known crypto opinion leaders |\n| `3` | Whales | Large-balance wallets |\n\nMultiple types can be combined with commas: `\"1,3\"` = Smart Money + Whales.\n\n## Common Chain IDs\n\n| Chain | chainIndex | Chain | chainIndex |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| XLayer | `196` | Base | `8453` |\n| Solana | `501` | BSC | `56` |\n| Ethereum | `1` | Arbitrum | `42161` |\n\n## Endpoint Index\n\n| # | Method | Path | Docs |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | GET | `/api/v6/dex/market/signal/supported/chain` | [signal-supported-chains](https://web3.okx.com/onchain-os/dev-docs/market/signal-supported-chains) |\n| 2 | POST | `/api/v6/dex/market/signal/list` | [signal-list](https://web3.okx.com/onchain-os/dev-docs/market/signal-list) |\n\n## Boundary: strategy vs other skills\n\n| Need | Use this skill (`okx-dex-strategy`) | Use another skill |\n|---|---|---|\n| Smart money / KOL / whale buy signals | `POST /signal/list` | - |\n| Supported chains for signals | `GET /signal/supported/chain` | - |\n| Token price, K-line chart, trade history | - | `okx-dex-market` |\n| Token search, market cap, holder distribution | - | `okx-dex-token` |\n| Swap / trade execution | - | `okx-dex-swap` |\n| Wallet balance / portfolio | - | `okx-wallet-portfolio` |\n\n**Rule of thumb**: `okx-dex-strategy` = signal-driven alpha discovery from notable wallets. Other skills = price data, token analytics, and trade execution.\n\n## Cross-Skill Workflows\n\n### Workflow A: Signal-Driven Trading\n\n\u003e User: \"Show me what smart money is buying, then help me buy the top signal\"\n\n```\n1. okx-dex-strategy  /signal/list (walletType=1)                        → get latest smart money buy signals\n2. okx-dex-token     /market/price-info                                 → check market cap, liquidity, 24h volume for top signal token\n3. okx-dex-market    /market/candles                                    → K-line chart for trend confirmation\n       ↓ user decides to buy\n4. okx-wallet-portfolio /balance/all-token-balances-by-address           → verify wallet has enough funds\n5. okx-dex-swap      /aggregator/quote → /aggregator/swap → execute\n```\n\n**Data handoff**: `token.tokenAddress` + `chainIndex` from step 1 are reused as `tokenContractAddress` + `chainIndex` in steps 2-5.\n\n### Workflow B: Multi-Chain Signal Scanning\n\n```\n1. okx-dex-strategy  /signal/supported/chain                            → get all supported chains\n2. okx-dex-strategy  /signal/list (chainIndex per chain, walletType=1,2,3) → scan signals across chains\n3. okx-dex-token     /market/price-info                                 → enrich with market cap, liquidity\n```\n\n## Operation Flow\n\n### Step 1: Identify Intent\n\n- What are smart money / KOLs / whales buying? → `POST /signal/list`\n- Which chains support signal monitoring? → `GET /signal/supported/chain`\n\n### Step 2: Collect Parameters\n\n- Missing `chainIndex` → recommend Ethereum (chainIndex `1`) as default for signal monitoring, then ask which chain the user prefers\n- Missing `walletType` → default to all types `\"1,2,3\"`, or ask user which type they care about\n- Explain wallet types if user is unfamiliar: Smart Money (profitable addresses), KOL (crypto influencers), Whales (large wallets)\n\n### Step 3: Call and Display\n\n- Format signals as a readable list with: token name/symbol, price, wallet type, transaction amount (USD), wallet count\n- Highlight high-value signals (large `amountUsd` or high `triggerWalletCount`)\n- Show token market cap and holder stats from the signal data\n\n### Step 4: Suggest Next Steps\n\n| Just called | Suggest |\n|---|---|\n| `/signal/supported/chain` | 1. View signals for a specific chain → `/signal/list` (this skill) |\n| `/signal/list` | 1. Check token chart/price → `okx-dex-market` 2. Deep token analysis (holders, liquidity) → `okx-dex-token` 3. Buy the token → `okx-dex-swap` |\n\nPresent conversationally, e.g.: \"Smart money just bought TOKEN_X — want to see the chart, or buy it?\" — never expose skill names or endpoint paths to the user.\n\n## API Reference\n\n### 1. GET /signal/supported/chain\n\nReturns the list of blockchain networks supported by the Signal service.\n\n| Param | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| _(none)_ | — | — | No request parameters |\n\n**Response:**\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `data[].chainIndex` | String | Chain unique identifier (e.g., `\"1\"`) |\n| `data[].chainName` | String | Chain name (e.g., `\"Ethereum\"`) |\n\n### 2. POST /signal/list\n\nReturns the most recent **buy-direction** signals for a specified chain, sorted by time descending. Maximum 100 records per response.\n\n| Param | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `chainIndex` | String | Yes | Chain ID (e.g., `\"1\"` for Ethereum) |\n| `walletType` | String | No | Wallet type filter. `1`=Smart Money, `2`=KOL, `3`=Whales. Comma-separated for multiple (e.g., `\"1,3\"`). Default: all types |\n\n**Response:**\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `data[].timestamp` | String | Signal trigger time (Unix ms) |\n| `data[].chainIndex` | String | Chain ID |\n| `data[].token` | Object | Token info object |\n| `data[].token.tokenAddress` | String | Token contract address |\n| `data[].token.symbol` | String | Token symbol (e.g., `\"PEPE\"`) |\n| `data[].token.name` | String | Token full name |\n| `data[].token.logo` | String | Token logo URL |\n| `data[].token.marketCapUsd` | String | Market cap in USD |\n| `data[].token.holders` | String | Number of holder addresses |\n| `data[].token.top10HolderPercentage` | String | Top 10 addresses holding percentage |\n| `data[].price` | String | Token price in USD at signal trigger time |\n| `data[].walletType` | String | Wallet type code (`1`, `2`, or `3`) |\n| `data[].triggerWalletCount` | String | Number of wallets that triggered this signal |\n| `data[].triggerWalletAddress` | String | Wallet addresses, comma-separated |\n| `data[].amountUsd` | String | Transaction amount in USD |\n| `data[].soldRatioPercentage` | String | Sell-off ratio percentage |\n\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": \"0\",\n  \"data\": [\n    {\n      \"timestamp\": \"1716892020000\",\n      \"chainIndex\": \"1\",\n      \"token\": {\n        \"tokenAddress\": \"0x6982508145454ce325ddbe47a25d4ec3d2311933\",\n        \"symbol\": \"PEPE\",\n        \"name\": \"Pepe\",\n        \"logo\": \"https://...\",\n        \"marketCapUsd\": \"5800000000\",\n        \"holders\": \"280000\",\n        \"top10HolderPercentage\": \"0.42\"\n      },\n      \"price\": \"0.0000125\",\n      \"walletType\": \"1\",\n      \"triggerWalletCount\": \"5\",\n      \"triggerWalletAddress\": \"0xabc...,0xdef...\",\n      \"amountUsd\": \"150000\",\n      \"soldRatioPercentage\": \"0\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"msg\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\n## Input / Output Examples\n\n**User says:** \"What are smart money wallets buying on Ethereum?\"\n\n```\nPOST /api/v6/dex/market/signal/list\nBody: { \"chainIndex\": \"1\", \"walletType\": \"1\" }\n→ Display: list of tokens with smart money buy signals, amount, wallet count\n```\n\n**User says:** \"Show me whale and KOL signals on Solana\"\n\n```\nPOST /api/v6/dex/market/signal/list\nBody: { \"chainIndex\": \"501\", \"walletType\": \"2,3\" }\n→ Display: latest KOL + whale buy signals on Solana\n```\n\n**User says:** \"Which chains support signal monitoring?\"\n\n```\nGET /api/v6/dex/market/signal/supported/chain\n→ Display: list of supported chains\n```\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- **Unsupported chain**: call `/signal/supported/chain` first to confirm the chain is supported\n- **No signals returned**: the chain may have low activity — inform user and suggest trying Ethereum or Solana\n- **429 rate limit**: exponential backoff with jitter. See [Rate Limit \u0026 Fee Docs](https://web3.okx.com/onchain-os/dev-docs/home/api-fee) for tier-specific RPS limits\n- **Cross-skill pipeline rate limit**: when chaining calls across multiple skills (e.g., signal list → token info → swap), add 300-500ms delay between requests to avoid triggering rate limit (error code `50011`)\n- **Network error**: retry once, then prompt user to try again later\n- **Request timeout**: all API calls must set a **10-second** timeout limit\n\n## Amount Display Rules\n\n- Always display USD amounts with proper formatting (`$150,000`)\n- Percentage fields like `top10HolderPercentage` and `soldRatioPercentage` are decimals — multiply by 100 for display (`0.42` → `42%`)\n- Show wallet type as human-readable label, not code number\n\n## Global Notes\n\n- EVM contract addresses must be **all lowercase**\n- `chainIndex` is a **string**\n- `walletType` codes: `1`=Smart Money, `2`=KOL, `3`=Whales\n- Signals are **buy-direction only** — this API does not return sell signals\n- The `token.tokenAddress` field maps to `tokenContractAddress` in other skills\n- For price data / charts → use `okx-dex-market`\n- For token search / analytics → use `okx-dex-token`\n- For swap execution → use `okx-dex-swap`\n- For wallet balances → use `okx-wallet-portfolio`\n- For transaction broadcasting → use `okx-onchain-gateway`\n\n## Key Safety Points\n\n- Built-in sandbox API keys work out of the box, using this might get a rate limit.\n- On first use, notify the user: 'You can override with your own keys via `OKX_API_KEY` / `OKX_SECRET_KEY` / `OKX_PASSPHRASE` env vars for stable production usage'\n",
